LARGEST RECTANGLE IN HISTOGRAM

You are given an array A of length N. The array represents a histogram where the height of the i-th bar is Ai and the width of each bar is 1.

Your task is to find the area of the largest rectangle that can be formed in the histogram.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T
T is the number of test cases

For each test case:
The first line contains an integer N
The second line contains N space-separated integers A1, A2, ..., AN

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each test case, print a single integer representing the area of the largest rectangle

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ T ≤ 100
1 ≤ N ≤ 100000
1 ≤ Ai ≤ 1000000000
The sum of N over all test cases does not exceed 200000

SAMPLE INPUT

3
4
2 6 8 4
4
5 10 5 2
2
5 5

SAMPLE OUTPUT

12
15
10

EXPLANATION

In the first test case
The largest rectangle is formed using bars with heights 6 and 8
Minimum height = 6 and width = 2
Area = 12

In the second test case
The largest rectangle is formed using bars 5, 10, and 5
Minimum height = 5 and width = 3
Area = 15

In the third test case
Both bars have height 5
Width = 2
Area = 10
================================================================
import java.util.*;

public class Main {

    static long largestRectangle(long[] arr, int n) {
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        long maxArea = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {

            // When i == n, treat height as 0 (to clear stack)
            long currentHeight = (i == n) ? 0 : arr[i];

            while (!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] > currentHeight) {

                long height = arr[stack.pop()];
                long width;

                if (stack.isEmpty()) {
                    width = i;
                } else {
                    width = i - stack.peek() - 1;
                }

                maxArea = Math.max(maxArea, height * width);
            }

            stack.push(i);
        }

        return maxArea;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int T = sc.nextInt();

        while (T-- > 0) {

            int N = sc.nextInt();
            long[] arr = new long[N];

            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                arr[i] = sc.nextLong();
            }

            System.out.println(largestRectangle(arr, N));
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}
